net.dragondelve.customdriversutil.gui.editor

Class DriverEditor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dragondelve.customdriversutil.gui.editor.DriverEditor

  • public class DriverEditor
extends java.lang.Object
    Driver Editor is designed to edit a single driver or a single track specific override if it is put into trackOverrideMode. This is a controller for the fxml/editor/DriverEditor.fxml.

      • editedDriver

        private DriverBase editedDriver
        Driver that is currently being edited by this editor. His properties are bound bidirectionally to the controls, and they have to be unbound with unbindDriver(Driver driver) if the value changes.

      • overrideMode

        private final javafx.beans.property.BooleanProperty overrideMode
        A flag that determines whether this editor is run in the trackOverride mode or not. This flag should be set to true if you want to edit a trackOverride. When setting this flag you have to already have set a driver, and you need to provide a track or a String value of an xmlName of the track that is going to be actually edited.

      • liveryNameChoiceBox

        private final javafx.scene.control.ChoiceBox<java.lang.String> liveryNameChoiceBox
        Choice box that allows the user to choose the driver's livery from the list instead of typing it. Is a part of HybridChoiceHBox. it is only displayed if the CheckBox inside HybridChoiceHBox is selected.

      • vehicleClass

        private final VehicleClass vehicleClass
        Vehicle Class of the edited driver.

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public void initialize()
        Initialize method initializes all the visual elements before they are displayed by the user. initialize method is called automatically by JavaFX when this editor is being loaded from XML.

      • setEditedDriver

        public void setEditedDriver(DriverBase driver)
        NOT a lightweight mutator method, unbinds the previous driver's properties and binds the new driver to the control elements of this editor.
        Parameters:
        driver - Driver to be edited.

      • setVehicleClass

        public void setVehicleClass(VehicleClass vehicleClass)
        Semi-lightweight mutator method.
        Parameters:
        vehicleClass - Vehicle class of the edited driver/

      • bindDriver

        private void bindDriver(DriverBase driver)
        Binds the given driver's properties to the control elements that are supposed to edit them. The bind will be done bidirectionally, and you should call unbindDriver on the same driver after it is no longer being edited.
        Parameters:
        driver - a driver whose properties are to be bind to the control elements of this editor.

      • unbindDriver

        private void unbindDriver(DriverBase driver)
        Unbinds the given driver's properties from the control elements of the editor. The bind will be unbound bidirectionally. If a driver was bound with bindDriver then you should unbind it with this method.
        Parameters:
        driver - a driver whose properties are to be unbound from the control elements of this editor.

      • bindBaseProperties

        private void bindBaseProperties(DriverBase driver)
        Binds all base properties that are shared between the Driver and TrackOverride. called from within bindDriver
        Parameters:
        driver - a driverbase whose properties re to be bound to the control elements of theis editor.

      • unbindBaseProperties

        private void unbindBaseProperties(DriverBase driver)
        Unbinds all base properties that are shared between the Driver and TrackOverride. called from within umbindDriver
        Parameters:
        driver - a driverbase whose properties re to be unbound to the control elements of theis editor.
